args: I brought treats from Hinomoto called\n＂rakugan.＂ They're something of a\nstandard offering for the departed.
You always did love your sweets,\nso I'm sure you will enjoy them.
Now where was I...? Ah, yes. I drifted to\nNorth Grastaea and found myself without\nfood, which meant I needed work.
My only marketable skill was my ability\nin battle, so it was only natural that I\nbecame a wandering mercenary.
Several years after I drifted to North Grastaea...
We got fiends blocking the road!\nTurn back, now!
We can't! We're pinned in by the\nwagons behind us!
Looks like I'm up. Stay back.\nThis will be dangerous.
Hey, you there! Out of the way!\nWagon coming through! Haaaah!
We should be good to pass now.
What fortune that I hired you on\nas a bodyguard, Khan.
No need for thanks. It's my job.

That name Khan, which you know well, was 
something I took on for work. I thought a person
with a name styled like the locals would be more
approachable, which would lead to more offers
of work.
We'll make camp here for the day, Khan.\nKeep watch while we inspect the cargo.
Forgive me, Captain, but might I be\nexcused from inspection duty?
Huh? Oh, right. It's almost her\nfeeding time. Well, you can keep watch\nwith Khan while you do it, all right?
There there. Drink up, little one.
My baby sister. Our parents died\nright after she was born.
So you're raising her? That's decent of you.

Well, I don't FEEL decent. She keeps me up
all night, and with all the caravan work,
I sometimes find myself thinking of her
as nothing but a...burden.
Don't be hard on yourself; everyone in\nyour position has such negative thoughts\nfrom time to time. You are a good brother.
Hmm? What is it, Sis? You wanna play\nwith that iron tube Khan is carrying?
You mean my tetsuhau? This is no toy,\nbut a weapon. I'm afraid I can't lend her\nsomething dangerous like this.
Well now, that's a curious shape for a\nweapon. How do you use it?

I don't know. It's a treasured heirloom
that has been passed down in my family
for generations, but someone forgot to
include instructions along the way.
I mostly use it to bash enemies in the\nface when my blade becomes dull.

Heh. Looks like someone is grumpy
because she can't fiddle with my deadly
weapon. How about we play instead?
Up, up, and awaaaay! Wheeee!

The next day, the caravan continued along
the mountain road toward its destination—
and I will forever regret that I didn't pay
more attention...
I scouted ahead and found\nno sign of fiends.
We'll continue on, then. The road is quite\nnarrow, so pass on the word to the wagons\nbehind us to be careful.
Easy there, Sis. What's wrong?\nWhy so upset all of a sudden?
It's like she's afraid of something...
Rocks! Rocks coming off the cliff!
Hellooooo? Anyone alive? Yoooo-hoo!\nLet us know so we can end yer misery!\nBwaaaa ha ha ha ha!
All right boys, start gatherin' anything\nwhat looks valuable and make sure to...\nOy, look at this pretty lady here!
Stones crushed her flat. Shame, that.
But her sword's in fine shape, so take it—\nand snatch up that iron tube while yer at it!
Oy, hold up! Did she just move?
Cor, are ya mad? She smashed to paste!\nNo way this one's drawin' breath.
I take it you're the curs who dropped\nthose boulders on us.
I got no idea what the hell's happenin',\nbut I killed ya once and I can do it again!\nTaaaaaake THIS!
Ha! Right in the sweet spot!\nSee ya in hell, girlie.
If you're quite done, it's time for you\nto pay for your foul deeds.
Blimey, she's still kickin'!\nWhat kinda monster IS this lady?!
This was how I came to understand\nwhat was happening to my body.
If I lost an arm, it grew back. If I lost a leg,\nI soon had replacement. If my heart stopped,\nit would restart in moments. I was...immortal.
This one's gone, too...\nLooks like I'm the only survivor...
Her brother shielded her with his body.
I knew you were a good one...
Easy, little one. Hello. I know that was\nscary, but you're all right now.
Let's pay our respects to the dead\nand then head to town.
